    "result": {"data":{"site":{"siteMetadata":{"title":"Scientific Excellence and Well Being - Unworkshop","author":"Scientific Excellence and Well Being"}},"markdownRemark":{"id":"d8b1ba63-806c-5d6b-accb-63c6cccf7606","excerpt":"You have amazing ideas but struggle to make them shine? Ideas pop up randomly\nin your head: you follow them, forget, see them pop up again? Or\ndo you use aâ€¦","html":"<p>You have amazing ideas but struggle to make them shine? Ideas pop up randomly\nin your head: you follow them, forget, see them pop up again? Or\ndo you use a diary, git repo, or org-mode file to store your ideas? While we\n(as scientists) sometimes track ideas conciously, our habits to evolve and\npolish ideas are rarely deliberate. Yet, sometimes we experience the perfect\nmoment: a whiteboard discussion, a blog article, a deep insight while taking a\nbath, ... and, suddently, a rough idea turns into a polished insight. Somehow,\nwe seem to know how to develop exquisite ideas!</p>\n<p>In this unworkshop, we will crowd-source best practices of how to evolve\nideas. By playing small and interactive games, we identify the critical steps\nthat we take when working with ideas. Together, we transform these small\nideas into 'science games', small deliberate activities which we can\nexperience, practice, and use deliberately whenever we encounter a new rough\nidea that may need some polishing.</p>\n<p>Join us for an experimental afternoon and play with us the science game.</p>\n<h2>Your Hosts</h2>\n<p><strong>Alexander Viand</strong></p>\n<p><span\n      class=\"gatsby-resp-image-wrapper\"\n      style=\"position: relative; display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto; max-width: 970px; \"\n    >\n      <a\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-link\"\n    href=\"/static/e9e9f876cd978e08dccbf88b8c822429/0d31c/alex.jpg\"\n    style=\"display: block\"\n    target=\"_blank\"\n    rel=\"noopener\"\n  >\n    <span\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-background-image\"\n    style=\"padd